Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.34,0:01:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask a historian,\N"What was mankind's greatest invention?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.63,0:01:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire? The wheel? The sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.55,0:01:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I would argue it's history itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.93,0:01:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,History isn't fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.23,0:01:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's narrative,\None carefully curated and shaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.52,0:01:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the pen strokes of the right scribe,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.07,0:01:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a villain becomes a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.82,0:01:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a lie becomes the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.20,0:01:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-Daddy?\N-Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:01:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-Where did we come from?\N-Trantor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.62,0:02:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did people come from\Nin the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.42,0:02:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of different theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.46,0:02:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them say that humans originally\Ninhabited a single planetary system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.63,0:02:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.43,0:02:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don't even know which.\NSirius, Alpha Centauri…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.76,0:02:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people think that we came\Nfrom some place called Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.93,0:02:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here. Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.90,0:02:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everyone we know about,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.11,0:02:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they also came from the same place?\NAnacreons and Thespins too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.49,0:02:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anacreons and Thespins too, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how can they hate us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.62,0:02:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Being human is complicated, Sal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.21,0:02:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We share a common origin\Nand some of the same myths.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're governed by this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In here is all the capacity\Nfor rational thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.14,0:03:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's sharing skull space\Nwith our emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes\Nemotions shout louder than logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.73,0:03:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody's emotions got real insistent\Nthat the Empire were doing them wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.19,0:03:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So they blew up the Star Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.11,0:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.16,0:03:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Violence is the last refuge\Nof the incompetent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.04,0:03:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they're not like us\Nat all then, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.17,0:03:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets loud up inside here too,\Ndoesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.75,0:03:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the thing, Sal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of people died\Nwhen that Star Bridge came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Empire killed many millions more\Non Anacreon and Thespis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.78,0:03:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And who won?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.07,0:03:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nobody?\N-Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.28,0:04:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how we know\Nthat the fall is bound to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Past behavior is the best predictor\Nof future performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.17,0:04:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor Hardin…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.35,0:04:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We're jumping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Lewis?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.32,0:05:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lewis, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.70,0:05:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Terminus?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.49,0:05:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.33,0:05:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We jumped back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.17,0:05:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Lewis?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.81,0:05:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:05:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You wished us home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.78,0:06:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.34,0:07:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Terminus Control, this is Salvor Hardin,\Non board the imperial warship Invictus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.02,0:07:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you read me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.77,0:07:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Terminus Control, do you read me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.77,0:07:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Salvor Hardin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.86,0:07:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Can anybody hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.46,0:07:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Salvor Hardin calling\Nthe Thespin lancers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.68,0:07:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Invictus jumped and we've dragged\Nyour ships into our quantum wake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.39,0:07:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in orbit around Terminus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.94,0:08:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can hear me, I have no idea\Nhow to stop this ship from jumping again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.98,0:08:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be an hour from now.\NIt could be days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.86,0:08:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I figure I'm stuck here, unless…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.10,0:08:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Beggar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get home?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.56,0:08:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take me through your route.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.28,0:08:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does this corridor go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.07,0:08:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The underground irrigation system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.91,0:08:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a path above it you could take\Nthrough the old palace ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.16,0:08:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up at the servants' exit,\Nright next to the palace gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I could exit here…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyperloop station's just there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Gate security has DNA scanners.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.30,0:09:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need the signal damper.\NFor my nanobots. So they can't track me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.97,0:09:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can get you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.06,0:09:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna die in this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.81,0:09:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.15,0:09:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't promise it'll all go right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.86,0:09:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can promise is\NI won't be the part that goes wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.70,0:09:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go. Brother Dusk is--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.24,0:09:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleon--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.28,0:09:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you had another name.\NOne that was just yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow you can give me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.09,0:09:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me that signal damper,\Nand I'll see you on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My apologies, Brother Dusk. I was--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.81,0:10:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.\NTime flows differently when you're young.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.03,0:10:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to share something with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my workplace, as you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.83,0:10:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The signature task of Dusk\Nis to record our visual history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.67,0:10:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The end of the Robot Wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Golden Horse Rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Each moment an inflection point\Nfor our dynasty,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.43,0:10:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when the fate of the galaxy\Nseemed to be hanging in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.52,0:10:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,As it did here…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.78,0:10:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when I chastened the barbarian worlds\Nfor their acts of savagery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.70,0:10:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And even while I was painting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.37,0:11:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was conscious of how we, as its authors,\Nwould be represented.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.92,0:11:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A clever artist provides commentary\Nwith his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.97,0:11:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even something as simple\Nas a choice of color
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.18,0:11:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,can convey a hidden meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.23,0:11:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes the moment's not so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.48,0:11:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it slips past us,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.73,0:11:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't even realize it\Nuntil it is past,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.03,0:11:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,until your debut on the wall is upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.70,0:11:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've painted you into our legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.05,0:11:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see\Nthe three ghillie raptors you shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.39,0:12:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've dreamed of one day doing something,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,anything, worthy enough\Nto be included in this mural.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.82,0:12:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why this small feat is…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.41,0:12:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm honored. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.41,0:12:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you had\Nthe greatness of Cleon I in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.63,0:12:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But during our hunt,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.71,0:12:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized there was something else\Ninside you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.35,0:12:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave you to reflect\Non your own glorious moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.10,0:12:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.40,0:12:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Appreciate the subtleties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.15,0:13:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What we choose\Nto tell our children and what we censor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.20,0:13:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What we illuminate and what we gloss over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.99,0:13:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,History as an act\Nof addition and subtraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.45,0:14:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire, you're needed\Nin the Principium Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.42,0:14:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't. I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.67,0:14:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dusk insists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm indisposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I need a minute alone,\Nand I'll come along. One minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.51,0:14:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I am also Empire, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.43,0:14:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.47,0:14:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But we both serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot something. I need to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.08,0:15:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It can wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.38,0:16:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Lock down the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.09,0:16:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let anyone in or out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a path you can take\Nthrough the palace ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.65,0:16:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up at the servants' exit,\Nright next to the palace gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.65,0:16:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This route takes you\Nto the underground irrigation system.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.66,0:16:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyperloop station's just there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Spread out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.28,0:17:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Warning. Water cycling imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.90,0:17:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Warning. Water cycling imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.15,0:17:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Four moons, that's a long jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:17:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.83,0:18:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Beggar, wake the hell up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.62,0:18:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome aboard, Captain Hardin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.66,0:19:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.29,0:20:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an imperial aura. For your jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.19,0:20:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me how to get\Nto the Desnian Sector on level 33?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.44,0:20:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the Cobalt Line down,\Nthen transfer to Ery Loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.33,0:20:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna head inner core.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.55,0:20:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Beggar, open a channel\Nto Terminus Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.72,0:21:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Communications channel open.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.51,0:21:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Terminus Control,\Nthis is Salvor Hardin. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.56,0:21:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.94,0:21:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Beggar, scan all frequencies.\NFind me anyone on comms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.23,0:21:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Scanning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.44,0:21:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No active comms detected
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.94,0:21:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,on the surface of Terminus.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.95,0:21:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You found someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.12,0:21:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Caution. Anomalous debris\Non potential intercept trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.58,0:21:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Threat level low.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.13,0:21:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.46,0:21:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Alert. Anomalous debris\Non confirmed intercept trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.80,0:21:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Threat level moderate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.38,0:21:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I need guns. Where are the guns?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.85,0:21:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Beggar, show me the guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.64,0:21:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Warning. Anomalous debris\Nobject impact imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.73,0:21:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Threat level severe. Warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.10,0:21:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Target locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.02,0:21:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Babe? Babe, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.15,0:21:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hugo, is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.79,0:22:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our plan worked, Sal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.38,0:22:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you get here from the Belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.72,0:22:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Luck, mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.09,0:22:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I made contact with Thespin Command.\NI rode shotgun on one of the lancers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.93,0:22:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I could see\Nthe Invictus was about to jump,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.27,0:22:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so I grabbed a sedation stick\Nand knocked myself out for the jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.61,0:22:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Warned the rest of my people\Nto do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.40,0:22:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I woke up to the dulcet tones\Nof your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.95,0:22:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't understand\Nhow you woke up so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.37,0:22:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I never went to sleep.\NIt's like the Vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.04,0:22:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't explain how or why,\Nbut the jump just didn't affect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.08,0:22:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So you got us back to Terminus?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.92,0:22:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that was Lewis.\NHe died to get us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.21,0:23:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Foundation's not responding?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.80,0:23:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No one is,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.68,0:23:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,not even the Anacreons Phara left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.97,0:23:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the null field.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.64,0:23:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel it, Hugo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.27,0:23:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's… even bigger. It's… louder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.44,0:23:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it's enveloped the whole planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.12,0:23:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.99,0:23:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they're all dead down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.00,0:23:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we just left? Right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.88,0:23:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make a run for the Red Corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.29,0:23:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you Irina Four,\NI'll show you Hesperus--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.21,0:23:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't, Hugo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.63,0:23:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there is no solution\Nto this crisis?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What if Seldon got it wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.40,0:24:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to see this through, Hugo.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.20,0:24:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.00,0:24:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.83,0:24:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Invictus is gonna jump again\Nunless your people can disable its drives.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.21,0:24:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let it jump. Let it take Phara.\NIt'll be out of our lives forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.76,0:24:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.26,0:24:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The Foundation needs that ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.51,0:24:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way we end the crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.68,0:24:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-I can't tell you how…\N-I just have a feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.61,0:24:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you have absolute faith in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.49,0:24:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You still believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.95,0:24:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind of a dick\Nif I changed my mind now, wouldn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.97,0:25:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see you on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.15,0:25:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.44,0:25:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.51,0:25:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You've lived every moment\Nof your life with people watching you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.85,0:25:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scar's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.48,0:26:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can lose yourself in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.90,0:26:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For Empire, the Scar represents a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.86,0:26:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For the rest of Trantor,\Nit represents an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.24,0:26:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.90,0:26:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we can look up and see\Nreal clouds, real stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.33,0:26:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not a simulation run by servers\Ndesigned to keep us complacent.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.18,0:26:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I live on level 33,\Nin the Desnian Sector.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.60,0:26:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Old Tertia makes the best\Nspiced malkas on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.36,0:26:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the corridor I take home.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.95,0:26:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing like your palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.41,0:26:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's chaotic. It's crowded.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.96,0:27:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.17,0:27:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.36,0:27:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.93,0:28:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not wearing your aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.19,0:28:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I traded it for this,\Nso I wouldn't be recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.23,0:28:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The jacket's smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.40,0:28:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can burn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.00,0:28:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to get my nanobots removed\Nin case they're tracking me. I…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.42,0:28:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably shouldn't even stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.59,0:28:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. I got the signal damper.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.68,0:28:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll cover you until we can arrange to…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.31,0:28:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.69,0:28:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The hardest part's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.11,0:29:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You got away from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.91,0:29:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.04,0:29:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But, truthfully…
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.00,0:29:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you still smell terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.55,0:29:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you shower?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.08,0:29:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I was thinking\Nabout a new name for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.26,0:30:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Azura?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.94,0:30:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.00,0:31:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Salvor,\Nthe engine room is that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.55,0:31:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got about thirty-three hours\Nto disable the jumpdrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.68,0:31:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.19,0:31:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A long and terrible story\Nthat no one's alive to tell…
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.65,0:31:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anacreons, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.65,0:31:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The bridge.\NSalvor has them tied up in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.57,0:31:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.17,0:32:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A wise man once said,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.09,0:32:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"A people without history\Nis like a tree without roots."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.06,0:32:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What's missing\Nfrom the wise man's history?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.72,0:32:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When did story replace record?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.23,0:32:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When all the facts\Nfall short of believability,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.86,0:32:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,fantasy feels reassuringly solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.91,0:32:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And since this is my history,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.70,0:32:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I get to decide\Nwhich parts have been subtracted,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.66,0:32:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which have been added.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.12,0:34:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jord?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.90,0:35:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom? Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.41,0:35:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom. Mom, wake up, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.58,0:35:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom. Mom, wake up, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.81,0:35:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you make anything of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.04,0:36:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. I'll figure it out myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.82,0:36:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your fists, Salvor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.95,0:36:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your fists, Salvor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.99,0:36:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.72,0:37:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you make anything of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.56,0:37:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor, if you were part of the Plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.27,0:37:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it would make it a lot easier\Nfor me to believe in all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.04,0:37:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How long did it take you…
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.87,0:37:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to trigger the Prime Radiant?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.00,0:37:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it on the second try.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.52,0:37:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,History is the ultimate weapon,\Nbecause it harnesses time itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.90,0:37:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Used correctly,\Nthe past can alter the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.28,0:37:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What other invention can do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.00,0:38:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.38,0:38:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.93,0:39:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-I thought I'd never see you again.\N-Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.40,0:39:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The null field, it's stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.12,0:39:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.96,0:39:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a door?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.13,0:39:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.68,0:39:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what now?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.64,0:39:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is where it ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.86,0:40:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find the Huntress?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.95,0:40:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We searched the entire ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.66,0:40:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No sign of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.91,0:40:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Except this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.24,0:40:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get down to Terminus\Nas fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.75,0:40:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Obsidian, open a channel\Nto Arkose and Gneiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.67,0:40:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Communications channel open.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.92,0:40:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Thespin Command.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.55,0:40:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I want all lancers planet-side\Nimmediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.72,0:40:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one of you is this ship slave to?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.19,0:40:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Slave this ship to Phara Keaen,\Nor you die too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.15,0:40:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Arkose, invoke protocol.\NShip transfer, Phara Keaen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.21,0:40:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart rate's rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.25,0:41:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If it gets to 120,\Nthen the bots go into crisis mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.47,0:41:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll increase the inhibitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.22,0:41:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Pulse is stabilizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.27,0:41:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Start the transfer now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.10,0:41:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're transferring your nanobots\Ninto my blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.56,0:42:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you wanted, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.69,0:42:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To have them removed?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.27,0:42:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.48,0:42:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A Dawn clone, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.61,0:42:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Superficially identical to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.53,0:42:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But how are you…
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.41,0:42:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here? Instead of floating in an aquarium?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.08,0:42:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people managed to smuggle\Nsome of Cleon I's DNA out of the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.42,0:42:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been working\Ntowards this day for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.42,0:42:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You surprised us.\NWe'd planned to have you escape tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.05,0:42:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Azura?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.23,0:42:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This was all a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.44,0:42:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you do this to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.19,0:42:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.32,0:42:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about the rest of the galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.53,0:42:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all the planets and people who've\Nbeen crushed under the Empire's heel.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.74,0:42:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not his fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.33,0:43:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how he was raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.29,0:43:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his brothers have always been told
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.63,0:43:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they are the light that never dims,\Nan unbroken chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.67,0:43:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality just doesn't penetrate\Ntheir little terrarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.60,0:43:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you're gonna stomach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.85,0:43:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.85,0:43:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been practicing my role long enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.94,0:43:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the cloistered little tyrant\Nin the making…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.65,0:43:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,projecting that subtle air\Nof self-pitying, arrogant indifference.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.82,0:43:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Practicing? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.37,0:43:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"Practicing? What are you talking about?"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.96,0:43:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm your understudy, Dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.88,0:43:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's time\Nfor me to take center stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.96,0:43:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go back to the palace,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.26,0:43:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm gonna be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.39,0:43:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll just kill you then.\NThey know I'm different.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.26,0:44:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.52,0:44:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.39,0:44:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not color-blind. I'm not left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.77,0:44:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm genetically identical to Cleon I.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.07,0:44:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.16,0:44:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.53,0:44:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be identical to the first,\Nand I'm not?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.62,0:44:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic nanoparticle transfection"\Nis the technical term.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.58,0:44:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all a little over my head,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.50,0:44:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but, basically, they altered your DNA\Nafter the fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.25,0:44:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, this has been planned since\Nbefore you or I took our first breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.84,0:44:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people knew they had to get you\Nout of the palace,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.64,0:44:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but they couldn't just take you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.93,0:44:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That would've been too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.06,0:44:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to make it\Nso you'd choose to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.23,0:44:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You needed a motive to run.\NAnd what better motive than survival?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.19,0:44:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the ones\Nwho made you different, Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.16,0:45:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In a certain way, you're lucky too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.33,0:45:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The Genetic Dynasty's\Nan affront to humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.66,0:45:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're no longer part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.75,0:45:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You never really were.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.67,0:45:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The transfer's complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.62,0:45:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You had no choice in any of this…
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.16,0:45:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but thank you just the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.80,0:45:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Get him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.89,0:46:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna do to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.64,0:46:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Cleon?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.29,0:46:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Azura. Azura, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.06,0:46:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.44,0:46:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dusk! I am so grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.74,0:47:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a full memory audit\Nof all the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.20,0:47:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.45,0:47:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.25,0:47:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.00,0:47:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a pleasure to observe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.05,0:47:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tailored though it was\Nto the young and foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.69,0:47:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't really think\Nwe'd let this drone leave the palace
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.98,0:47:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,without alerting us, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.98,0:47:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We followed your whole\Nenticing travelogue home, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.16,0:47:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You let him get away\Nso he would lead you to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.12,0:47:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Shroud her.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.19,0:48:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You got what you wanted then.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.02,0:48:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Never presume to understand what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.41,0:48:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You are stupid, naive, gullible.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.00,0:48:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So was I at your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.91,0:48:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And these things are forgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.67,0:48:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But the matter of your… difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.13,0:48:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's rather more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.67,0:48:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But you must've heard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.68,0:48:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a victim. We all are.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.43,0:48:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.89,0:48:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes you\Nthe embodiment of our vulnerability,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.35,0:48:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an ugly reminder of the knife-edge
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.06,0:49:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,upon which\Nour Genetic Dynasty is balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.36,0:49:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,By what logic would we want\Nto look on your face ever again?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.20,0:49:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My face?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.08,0:49:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My face is your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.66,0:49:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget logic. Try empathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.47,0:49:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.34,0:49:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely it's not up to you. It's up to Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.85,0:49:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.48,0:49:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Day will be home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.90,0:49:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can plead your case to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.69,0:49:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt his experience on the Maiden\Nhas made him serene.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.04,0:49:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Warden, you made it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.54,0:49:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your distance, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.21,0:50:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But everyone's waking up. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.46,0:50:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not over.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.05,0:50:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor, wait. Don't go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.63,0:50:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.76,0:50:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You will not! Step away.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.18,0:50:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You said this wasn't a trick,\Nthat you didn't know what this was.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.47,0:50:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.56,0:50:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet your daughter has tamed it.\NHow do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.33,0:51:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Sal.\NI tried to talk 'em out of landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.13,0:51:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.05,0:51:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where I'm supposed to be.\NEverything converging in a single crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.55,0:51:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is our Huntress?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.72,0:51:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She lost control of the Invictus.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.39,0:51:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your plans for martyrdom, for Trantor,\Nthey're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.23,0:51:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowan?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.31,0:51:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Weald Gods have forsaken us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.35,0:52:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hammered shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.53,0:52:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't this a pretty picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.95,0:52:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemies old and new,\Nconveniently gathered in one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.38,0:52:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop your weapons and unbind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.09,0:53:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Warden, don't even think\Nabout flashing that coin of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.43,0:53:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you're alive, Phara, truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.77,0:53:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.86,0:53:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Last thing I'm interested in hearing\Nis more words from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.36,0:53:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Phara, please. The jump induces psychosis.\NYou're not thinking straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.90,0:53:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.21,0:53:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Also aiming.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.46,0:53:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, if you don't like\Nwhat I have to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.67,0:53:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you can kill me when I'm done.\NYou can kill all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.51,0:53:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.01,0:53:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That ship…
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.26,0:53:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most powerful weapon\Nyour people will ever get their hands on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.48,0:53:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, why destroy it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.81,0:53:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why not use it for leverage?\N-How?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.48,0:53:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We band together, all three worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.74,0:53:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.03,0:54:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can share the Invictus.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.87,0:54:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We can repair it, together.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.00,0:54:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All we have to do is let our logic speak\Nlouder than our emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.67,0:54:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Phara, stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.09,0:54:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You would take up arms\Nagainst your own Huntress?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.97,0:54:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The hunt is over, Phara.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.53,0:54:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Phara, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.94,0:55:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-Take aim!\N-Freestone, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.82,0:55:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone. Drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.47,0:55:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.55,0:55:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anacreons, Thespins, and Termini.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.02,0:55:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing you all gathered here\Ngives me hope…
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.94,0:55:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we might actually pull this off.
